> > > > > >
> > > > > > One more question, please. The ball on the bottom of the shifter
has
> > a
> > > > little
> > > > > protrusion apparently to line it up/maintain alignment in the cup
of
> > the
> > > > front shift rod that it falls into.
> > > > > >
> > > > > > My protrusion seems too short.
> > > > > >
> > > > > > Did I just say that?
> > > > > >
> > > > > > How long should the protrusion be?
> > > > > >
> > > > > > Go easy on me.
> > > > > >
> > > > > > Billy
> > > > > >
> > > > > > >The rear rod goes thru a "tunnel"(a pipe).  The 2 bellows are
on
> > each
> > > > end of the pipe and seal the tunnel from the elements while the rod
goes
> > in
> > > > at the front and out in the rear.
> > > > > > >
> > > > > > >This tunnel/pipe is what the bushings ride inside of to help
keep
> > the
> > > > rod centered in the tunnel.
> > > > > > >
> > > > > > >Front and rear couple together in the front and then the rear
goes
> > > > > > >straight thru to the rear tranny coupler.
